The paper proposes a new data structure and a graph database management system for efficiently managing large graphs on disk. This falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also mentions the ability to execute powerful analytical graph computation, which could fall under information retrieval (cs.IR) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the ability to work with extremely large graphs on just a laptop or PC, which could fall under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
